00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:30.030
according to the study, the foreskin has it's
own microbiome!

00:02:30.030 --> 00:02:34.110
For the study, researchers from Johns Hopkins
Bloomberg School of Public Health looked under

00:02:34.110 --> 00:02:39.390
the hood of uncircumcised penises, and found
anaerobic bacteria, those are bacteria which

00:02:39.390 --> 00:02:40.560
live without oxygen.

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:46.220
Studying Ugandan men before and after circumcision,
they discovered, that this previously unknown

00:02:46.220 --> 00:02:53.690
anaerobic bacteria disappeared in the year
they were cut; forever altering the individual

00:02:53.690 --> 00:02:55.270
microbiome of the male penis.

00:02:55.270 --> 00:03:00.010
It is known from other studies that Langerhans
cells normally live under the foreskin as

00:03:00.010 --> 00:03:04.980
well, and are commonly attacked by HIV, so
perhaps that's why HIV transmission is so

00:03:04.980 --> 00:03:07.420
much lower with circumcised men?

00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:08.850
They're still figuring this out.

00:03:08.850 --> 00:03:13.620
In the end, the practice is ancient and fascinating,
but is it necessary?

00:03:13.620 --> 00:03:17.280
Not at all, and there's still a roaring debate
about removing a third of the penile erogenous

00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:31.540
